                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.51/3997</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued by the Department of State, May 5,
                        1934</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1934-05-05">May 5, 1934</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>With reference to the efforts of other governments to obtain preferential
                    treatment for their holders of German bonds, the American Embassy has informed
                    the German Government that the previously stated position of the United States
                    Government opposing discrimination against American bondholders remains
                    unchanged; and that careful consideration of the facts leads to the definite
                    conclusions that Germany has power to prevent special arrangements with the
                    different creditor countries and that it cannot escape the responsibility for
                    any preferences it may sanction.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
